version_semver_justification: The project does not require the ability to express the scenarios covered by semver wrt incompatible changes.
release_notes_justification: Each release has a formal changelog written https://wiki.qemu.org/ChangeLog/2.10
release_notes_vulns_justification: The project does not yet identify security flaws in a formal manner
build_common_tools_justification: The project uses GNU Make and GCC/CLang & Python
build_floss_tools_justification: The project uses GNU Make and GCC/CLang & Python
test_justification: Unit tests & functional tests are in the main source repo https://git.qemu.org/?p=qemu.git;a=tree;f=tests;hb=HEAD
test_invocation_justification: It can be run with 'make check'
test_most_justification: The test suite does not yet have broad enough coverage
test_policy_justification: New functionality is encouraged to have test coverage, where pratical to test it given current test infrastructure
tests_are_added_justification: Major features often come with test coverage
warnings_justification: Multiple compiler warning options are enabled
warnings_fixed_justification: The project aims to be free of warnings on all major platforms
know_secure_design_justification: It is a core competency of many members of the dev team
know_common_errors_justification: It is a core competency of many members of the dev team
crypto_published_justification: The project relies on respected 3rd party libraries for crypto where ever possible and only uses quality algorithms unless required otherwise for interoperability
crypto_call_justification: The TCG code generator uses custom AES impls since the CPU instruction emulator requires fine grained access to AES internals not exposed by 3rd party libraries. The rest of the code uses 3rd party libraries for crypto routines.
crypto_keylength_justification: The crypto relies on GNUTLS defaults configurable via system policy
crypto_working_justification: Any use of weak is strictly opt-in by the user
crypto_pfs_justification: The TLS services policy supports PFS by default
crypto_password_storage_justification: All persistent password storage is delegated to 3rd party libraries (SASL/Kerberos) which uses hashing/salting where appropriate
crypto_random_justification: Internal APIs provide access to cryptographically strong routines / sources
static_analysis_justification: The coverity tool is run against the codebase frequently
static_analysis_fixed_justification: Issues reported by coverity are fixed within days.
static_analysis_often_justification: Coverity is not yet run on an automated manner
dynamic_analysis_justification: Various compiler built-in analysis features are enabled and runtime instrumentation such as _FORTIFY_SOURCE are used
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: The project makes extensive use of assert()
crypto_weaknesses_justification: The crypto relies on GNUTLS defaults configurable via system policy
discussion_justification: https://wiki.qemu.org/MailingLists
